import math
cases = int(input())
for _ in range(cases):
    line = input().strip('\r\n')
    ss = line.split(' ')
    (n, k, b, s) = tuple([int(x) for x in ss])
    max_v = math.floor(s / k)
    min_v = math.floor((s - (n - 1) * (k - 1)) / k)
    if b < min_v or b > max_v:
        print('-1')
        continue
    if k == 1:
        ans = [0] * (n - 1) + [s]
    else:
        num = max_v - b
        v = s - num * (k - 1)
        while v // k > b:
            m = v // k - b
            num += m
            v = s - num * (k - 1)
        ans = [0] * (n - num - 1) + [k - 1] * num + [v]
    print(' '.join([str(x) for x in ans]))

t = int(input())
for _ in range(t):
    (n, k, b, s) = map(int, input().split())
    a = [0] * n
    if s // k < b:
        print(-1)
        continue
    border = (n - 1) * (k - 1)
    if (s - border) // k > b:
        print(-1)
        continue
    i = 0
    while s // k > b:
        a[i] = k - 1
        i += 1
        s -= k - 1
    a[i] = s
    print(*a)

t = int(input())
for i in range(t):
    nkb = list(map(int, input().split()))
    (n, k, b, s) = (nkb[0], nkb[1], nkb[2], nkb[3])
    stop = k * b
    stop2 = k * b + (k - 1) * n
    if stop > s or stop2 < s:
        print(-1)
    elif stop == s:
        print(*[0 for i in range(n - 1)] + [stop])
    else:
        m = [0 for i in range(n - 1)] + [stop]
        w = s - stop
        q = 0
        while w > k - 1:
            m[q] = m[q] + k - 1
            w = w - k + 1
            q += 1
        m[-1] = m[-1] + w
        print(*m)
